2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for cooperative spectrum sensing, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an algorithm for controlling the spectrum sensing process in Cognitive Radios. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the security implications of cooperative spectrum sensing in Cognitive Radios. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for cooperative spectrum sensing, which involves multiple agents (Cognitive Radios) working together.
